,{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuwrN","text_ar":"جَزُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) n. un. as above: (M: in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazorapN","text_ar":"جَزْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarapN","text_ar":"جَزَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, fit for slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, to which the owners betake themselves and which they slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is lawful to be slaughtered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarN","text_ar":"جَزَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is sometimes [written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizarN","text_ar":"جِزَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaru Als~ibaAEi","text_ar":"جَزَرُ السِّبَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flesh which beasts or birds of prey eat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakuwhumo jazarFA","text_ar":"تَرَكُوهُمْ جَزَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They slew them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they left them cut"},{"kind":"page_break","n":419},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in pieces"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lils~ibaAEi","text_ar":"لِلسِّبَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the beasts or birds of prey"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAruwA jazarFA liloEaduw~i","text_ar":"صَارُوا جَزَرًا لِلْعَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They became a prey to the enemy, cut in pieces"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaziyrapN","text_ar":"جَزِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiz~rN","text_ar":"جِزّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S, Msb, K,) the latter with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) arabicized, (K,) from the Persian ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Gazaro","text_ar":"گَزَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (AHn,) [coll. gen. ns., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Carrots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carrot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruwmap","text_ar":"اَرُومَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is eaten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarapN","text_ar":"جَزَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, S, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best kind is the red and sweet, which grows in winter: it is hot in the extreme of the second degree; moist in the first degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diuretic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lenitive; emollient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthening to the venereal faculty; emmenagogue: the putting of its pounded leaves upon festering ulcers is advantageous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is difficult of digestion; and engenders bad blood; but is made wholesome with vinegar and mustard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinozaAbN","text_ar":"حِنْزَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hzb","text_ar":"حزب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Fr","Msb","AHn","As"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}